# Hard Challenges

**Platform:** TryHackMe  
**Progress:** 0 / 100 Completed  
**Difficulty:** Hard  

---

## Overview

Hard challenges are the closest TryHackMe gets to real-world penetration testing 
complexity. Nothing is handed to you. Enumeration is deep, vulnerabilities are obscure, 
exploitation requires precise execution, and privilege escalation paths demand thorough 
understanding of operating system internals, Active Directory attack chains, 
or advanced web exploitation techniques.

These rooms are where offensive security skill is genuinely tested. A complete 
methodology, solid fundamentals across every domain, and the ability to research 
and adapt on the fly are all required. Hard rooms on TryHackMe are comparable in 
difficulty to OSCP-style machines and prepare directly for certification examinations 
and real client engagements.

This section is the current target — building toward it through medium challenges 
and continued path progression.

---

## Skills Required
- Deep Active Directory attack chains (Kerberoasting, AS-REP roasting, DCSync, 
  Pass-the-Hash, Pass-the-Ticket, Golden/Silver Ticket attacks)
- Advanced binary exploitation and reverse engineering
- Complex multi-pivot network environments
- Custom exploit development
- Advanced malware analysis and evasion
- Obscure privilege escalation vectors
- Full black-box enumeration with minimal guidance

